005package edu.wpi.first.units;
006
007/**
008 * Unit of mass dimension.
009 *
010 * <p>This is the base type for units of mass dimension. It is also used to specify the dimension
011 * for {@link Measure}: <code>Measure&lt;Mass&gt;</code>.
012 *
013 * <p>Actual units (such as {@link Units#Grams} and {@link Units#Pounds}) can be found in the {@link
014 * Units} class.
015 */
016public class Mass extends Unit<Mass> {
017  /** Creates a new unit with the given name and multiplier to the base unit. */
018  Mass(double baseUnitEquivalent, String name, String symbol) {
019    super(Mass.class, baseUnitEquivalent, name, symbol);
020  }
021
022  Mass(UnaryFunction toBaseConverter, UnaryFunction fromBaseConverter, String name, String symbol) {
023    super(Mass.class, toBaseConverter, fromBaseConverter, name, symbol);
024  }
025}
